Luis Suarez believes fate has pitted him against Real Madrid on his Barcelona debut.

The controversial former Liverpool striker is serving a ban for biting Italy's Giorgio Chiellini at the World Cup, but will be available for the grudge El Clasico clash on October 25.

The Uruguayan admitted he was surprised to learn he could make his debut in such an important game, but was adamant he will be up to the task.

