'It's a huge coincidence but I'm looking forward to the experience,' Suarez told Barca Magazine.

'You know, I'm the kind of person who believes that things happen for a reason, and of all 19 teams in the league, it's precisely against Real Madrid at the Bernabeu that I'll make my comeback. There must be a reason.'

Their was some surprise when Barcelona spent so much money on Suarezd espite the fact that he was serving a lengthy suspension, but the 27-year-old is determined to repay the faith.

'All I can say is that I have arrived with the desire to be a success at Barca that I am hungry to win titles,' Suarez said.

'I have the chance to play for the team that I have always wanted to play for and it's a chance I intend to make the most of. I want to show the fans that I want to be a success at Barca and to help my team mates as much as I can.'

